Name: UCSB
Description: UCSB is a prestigious public school in the University of California system. The campus has a beautiful landscape and a large student body.

Name: Lake Cachuma
Description: Lake Kachuma is a scenic lake on the California side of the highway where many travelers can have a picnic.

Name: Griffith observatory
Description: The Griffith Observatory is located high above the city, offering not only a panoramic view of Los Angeles but also the opportunity to observe stars or other celestial events with specialized instruments.

Name: San Francisco zoo
Description: San Francisco zoo is a large park in California with about 250 species of animals. And the famous gorilla Coco was born here.

Name: Universal Studio Hollywood
Description: Thhe universal studio hollywood is a large thhemne park wit many large entertainment facilities for visitors to play.

Name: Getty center
Description: The Getty Center overlooks all of Los Angeles and has many nineteenth-century American, European, and Asian art collections on display.
